    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-11-15T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-11-15T13:00:00-05:00" n="116"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d116">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112/5525</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Delegate to the Inter-Allied Council</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_COT1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Crosby</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-11-15T18:00:00+00:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 15, 1917, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 9.30 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>No. 4 for Secretary of the Treasury:</p>
                <p>The Treasury here reports that financial embargo plan presented by British
                    Government has been favorably considered in Washington. There are serious
                    objections to this plan. It is now being studied here. <persName
                        corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_CPD1">Cravath</persName> and American bankers
                    and some English bankers who have been consulted agree that modifications should
                    be worked out before our Government joins in the plan as proposed. Will wire you
                    further on this in a few days.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_COT1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Crosby</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
